mill massacre">Kingsmill massacre</a>&#160;–</span> <span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/La_Mon_restaurant_bombing" title="La Mon restaurant bombing">La Mon restaurant bombing</a>&#160;–</span> <span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/Warrenpoint_ambush" title="Warrenpoint ambush">Warrenpoint ambush</a>&#160;–</span> <span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/Dunmurry_train_explosion" title="Dunmurry train explosion">Dunmurry explosion</a>&#160;–</span> <span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/1981_Irish_hunger_strike" title="1981 Irish hunger strike">Hunger Strike</a>&#160;–</span> <span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/Glasdrumman_ambush" title="Glasdrumman ambush">Glasdrumman ambush</a>&#160;–</span> <span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/Attacks_on_shipping_in_Lough_Foyle_(1981-1982)" title="Attacks on shipping in Lough Foyle (1981-1982)">Lough Foyle attacks</a>&#160;–</span> <span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/Droppin_Well_bombing" title="Droppin Well bombing">Droppin Well bombing</a>&#160;–</span> <span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/Maze_Prison_escape" title="Maze Prison escape">Maze Prison escape</a>&#160;–</span> <span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/1985_Newry_mortar_attack" title="1985 Newry mortar attack">Newry mortar attack</a>&#160;–</span> <span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/Attack_on_Ballygawley_barracks" title="Attack on Ballygawley barracks">Ballygawley barracks</a>&#160;–</span> <span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/Remembrance_Day_bombing" title="Remembrance Day bombing">Remembrance Day bombing</a>&#160;–</span> <span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/Milltown_Cemetery_attack" title="Milltown Cemetery attack">Milltown Cemetery attack</a>&#160;–</span> <span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/Corporals_killings" title="Corporals killings">Corporals killings</a>&#160;–</span> <span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/Attack_on_Derryard_checkpoint" title="Attack on Derryard checkpoint">Derryard checkpoint</a>&#160;–</span> <span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/Operation_Conservation" title="Operation Conservation">Operation Conservation</a>&#160;–</span> <span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/Glenanne_barracks_bombing" title="Glenanne barracks bombing">Glenanne barracks</a>&#160;–</span> <span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/Attack_on_Cloghogue_checkpoint" title="Attack on Cloghogue checkpoint">Cloghogue checkpoint</a>&#160;–</span> <span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/South_Armagh_Sniper_(1990%E2%80%931997)" title="South Armagh Sniper (1990–1997)">South Armagh Snipers</a>&#160;–</span> <span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/Shankill_Road_bombing" title="Shankill Road bombing">Shankill bombing</a>&#160;–</span> <span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/Greysteel_massacre" title="Greysteel massacre">Greysteel massacre</a>&#160;–</span> <span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/Drumcree_conflict" title="Drumcree conflict">Drumcree conflict</a>&#160;–</span> <span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/Omagh_bombing" title="Omagh bombing">Omagh bombing</a>&#160;–</span> <span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/Holy_Cross_dispute" title="Holy Cross dispute">Holy Cross dispute</a><br />
<i><b><a href="/wiki/England" title="England">England</a></b></i><br />
<a href="/wiki/1972_Aldershot_bombing" title="1972 Aldershot bombing" class="mw-redirect">Aldershot bombing</a>&#160;–</span> <span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/M62_coach_bombing" title="M62 coach bombing">Coach bombing</a>&#160;–</span> <span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/Guildford_pub_bombings" title="Guildford pub bombings">Guildford bombings</a>&#160;–</span> <span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/Birmingham_pub_bombings" title="Birmingham pub bombings">Birmingham bombings</a>&#160;–</span> <span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/Balcombe_Street_siege" title="Balcombe Street siege" class="mw-redirect">Marylebone siege</a>&#160;–</span> <span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/Hyde_Park_and_Regents_Park_bombings" title="Hyde Park and Regents Park bombings">Hyde and Regents Park bombings</a>&#160;–</span> <span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/Harrods_bombing" title="Harrods bombing">Harrods bombing</a>&#160;–</span> <span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/Brighton_hotel_bombing" title="Brighton hotel bombing">Brighton bombing</a>&#160;–</span> <span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/1989_Deal_barracks_bombing" title="1989 Deal barracks bombing">Deal bombing</a>&#160;–</span> <span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/Warrington_bomb_attacks" title="Warrington bomb attacks">Warrington bombings</a>&#160;–</span> <span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/1993_Bishopsgate_bombing" title="1993 Bishopsgate bombing">Bishopsgate bombing</a>&#160;–</span> <span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/1996_Docklands_bombing" title="1996 Docklands bombing">Docklands bombing</a>&#160;–</span> <span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/1996_Manchester_bombing" title="1996 Manchester bombing">Manchester bombing</a>&#160;–</span> <span style="white-space:nowrap"><a href="/wiki/3_August_2001_Ealing_bombing" title="3 August 2001 Ealing bombing">Ealing bombing</a></span></p>
</div>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p><b>The Troubles</b> (<a href="/wiki/Irish_language" title="Irish language">Irish</a>: <span lang="ga" xml:lang="ga"><i>Na Trioblóidí</i></span>) was a period of ethno-political<sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2" title=""><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-3" title=""><span>[</span>4<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-4" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-4" title=""><span>[</span>5<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-5" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-5" title=""><span>[</span>6<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-6" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-6" title=""><span>[</span>7<span>]</span></a></sup> conflict in <a href="/wiki/Northern_Ireland" title="Northern Ireland">Northern Ireland</a> which spilled over at various times into <a href="/wiki/England" title="England">England</a>, the <a href="/wiki/Republic_of_Ireland" title="Republic of Ireland">Republic of Ireland</a> and <a href="/wiki/Continental_Europe" title="Continental Europe">mainland Europe</a>. The duration of the Troubles is conventionally dated from the late 1960s and considered by many to have ended with the <a href="/wiki/Belfast_Agreement" title="Belfast Agreement">Belfast Agreement</a> of 1998.<sup id="cite_ref-7" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-7" title=""><span>[</span>8<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-Hope_8-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Hope-8" title=""><span>[</span>9<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-9" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-9" title=""><span>[</span>10<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-10" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-10" title=""><span>[</span>11<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-11" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-11" title=""><span>[</span>12<span>]</span></a></sup> Violence nonetheless continues on a sporadic basis.<sup id="cite_ref-12" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-12" title=""><span>[</span>13<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-13" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-13" title=""><span>[</span>14<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-Hope_8-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Hope-8" title=""><span>[</span>9<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p>The principal issues at stake in the Troubles were the <a href="/wiki/Partition_of_Ireland" title="Partition of Ireland">constitutional status of Northern Ireland</a> and the relationship between the mainly-Protestant <a href="/wiki/Unionism_in_Ireland" title="Unionism in Ireland">Unionist</a> and mainly-Catholic <a href="/wiki/Irish_nationalism" title="Irish nationalism">Nationalist</a> communities in Northern Ireland. The Troubles had both political and military (or paramilitary) dimensions. Its participants included politicians and political activists on both sides, <a href="/wiki/Irish_republicanism" title="Irish republicanism">republican</a> and <a href="/wiki/Ulster_loyalism" title="Ulster loyalism">loyalist</a> <a href="/wiki/Paramilitary" title="Paramilitary">paramilitaries</a>, and the security forces of the United Kingdom and the Republic of Ireland.</p>
