<li id="cite_note-100"><b><a href="#cite_ref-100" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://cain.ulst.ac.uk/sutton/chron/1975.html" class="external text" title="http://cain.ulst.ac.uk/sutton/chron/1975.html" rel="nofollow">"CAIN: Sutton Index of Deaths"</a>. Cain.ulst.ac.uk<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://cain.ulst.ac.uk/sutton/chron/1975.html" class="external free" title="http://cain.ulst.ac.uk/sutton/chron/1975.html" rel="nofollow">http://cain.ulst.ac.uk/sutton/chron/1975.html</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-11-02</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=CAIN%3A+Sutton+Index+of+Deaths&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.pub=Cain.ulst.ac.uk&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fcain.ulst.ac.uk%2Fsutton%2Fchron%2F1975.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:The_Troubles"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span><br />
*27 July 1975 William Hanna (46) Protestant Status: Ulster Volunteer Force (UVF), Killed by: Ulster Volunteer Force (UVF) Also off duty Ulster Defence Regiment (UDR) member. Shot outside his home, Houston Park, Mourneview, Lurgan, County Armagh.
<ul>
<li>31 July 1975 Harris Boyle (22) Protestant</li>
</ul>
Status: Ulster Volunteer Force (UVF), Killed by: Ulster Volunteer Force (UVF) Also Ulster Defence Regiment member. Killed in premature explosion while planting bomb on minibus belonging to Miami showband, Buskhill, near Newry, County Down.
<ul>
<li>31 July 1975 Wesley Somerville (34) Protestant</li>
</ul>
Status: Ulster Volunteer Force (UVF), Killed by: Ulster Volunteer Force (UVF) Also Ulster Defence Regiment member. Killed in premature explosion while planting bomb on minibus belonging to Miami showband, Buskhill, near Newry, County Down.</li>
<li id="cite_note-101"><b><a href="#cite_ref-101" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://cain.ulst.ac.uk/sutton/chron/1972.html" class="external text" title="http://cain.ulst.ac.uk/sutton/chron/1972.html" rel="nofollow">"CAIN: Sutton Index of Deaths"</a>. Cain.ulst.ac.uk<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://cain.ulst.ac.uk/sutton/chron/1972.html" class="external free" title="http://cain.ulst.ac.uk/sutton/chron/1972.html" rel="nofollow">http://cain.ulst.ac.uk/sutton/chron/1972.html</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2009-03-13</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=CAIN%3A+Sutton+Index+of+Deaths&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.pub=Cain.ulst.ac.uk&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fcain.ulst.ac.uk%2Fsutton%2Fchron%2F1972.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:The_Troubles"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span><br />
*17 October 1972 John Todd (23) Protestant Status: Ulster Defence Association (UDA), Killed by: British Army (BA) Also off duty Ulster Defence Regiment (UDR) member. Shot during street disturbances, Wilton Street, Shankill, Belfast.</li>
